a few years ago , here at ted , peter skill , a design contest called " the marshmallow challenge . "
the idea is pretty simple . four teams must be the greatest freestanding structure with 20 spaghetti , about 1 m duct tape , build a 1 m thread and a marshmallow .
the marshmallow must be on top .
and , although it seems really simple , it 's actually really hard , because it pushes people work very quickly .
and so i thought that this is an interesting idea , and i 've turned it into a design workshop .
it was a tremendous success .
since then , i 've done about 70 workshops around the world , with students , developers and architects , even with ctos fortune 50 companies , and there 's something in this task , what deep insights into the nature of cooperation , and i want to share with you some of them .
normally , most people start to orient themselves to the task .
they talk about it , they consider how it will look , they jockey for power .
then you invest a little time in planning and organization . they outline and put spaghetti .
they invest most of their time in the assembly of increasing structures
and finally , shortly before they 've run out of time , someone takes the marshmallow and they bring it back to the top , take a step back and " ta da ! " they admire their work .
but then , almost always , what happens is that the " ta da " to a " uh oh " is because of the weight of the marshmallows that bridge , and the whole thing will fall down .
there are a number of people who are much more " uh oh " moments than others , and among the worst are fresh graduates go to business school .
they lie , they cheat , they are really confused and produce a meager entity .
and of course , there are teams that much more " ta da " entity , and are among the best fresh graduates of the kindergarten .
and that 's pretty amazing .
as peter told us they don 't produce only the highest towers , but also the most interesting structures of all .
you might be wondering what is : how come ? why ? what about that ?
and tells peter : " none of the children to be invested time to head the spaghetti gmbh . "
they don 't have time to invest in power struggles .
but there is another reason .
and that is that have been trained to business school students , to find a plan , ok !
and to do it .
then what happens when you put the marshmallow on the tip , they 've run out of time , and what happens ?
